text: Proterodesma byrsopola is a species of moth in the family Tineidae. It was described by Edward Meyrick in 1909. This species is endemic to New Zealand. ==References== ==External links== *Image of type specimen of Proterodesma byrsopola Category:Moths described in 1909 Category:Tineidae Category:Moths of New Zealand Category:Endemic fauna of New Zealand Category:Taxa named by Edward Meyrick
